ckets</a> that I&#x2019;m seeing everywhere lately&#x2014;but I have narrow shoulders. Can I pull off a blazer like that even if I&#x2019;m crazy thin?</strong><br>[Holds fist in the air in solidarity] We scrawny fellows don&apos;t always have it easy. I have two or three wide-lapel blazers and suit jackets, so I&apos;m for the look. But there are some that just don&apos;t work with the <a href="http://i.cdn.turner.com/si/multimedia/photo_gallery/1204/rare.reggie.miller.pics/images/reggie-miller.jpg">Reggie Miller body type</a>. I know now that if I try on the jacket and the lapels look more like wings sprouting from my chest, I move on. The worst thing you can do is buy the jacket and hope it grows on you. (The second-worst thing: asking a tailor to slim the lapels, which never works.) Good style is like batting. Knowing which pitches not to swing at is half the battle. </p><div class="embed hr" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.4.1"><hr></div><div class="embed callout" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.4.2"><div class="callout small" data-type="callout"><figure class="embedded-image" data-type="image"><div class="image-content"><div class="component-rendition"><div class="component-image loaded"><span><img src="http://media.gq.com/photos/56030a7a00a6dc503f9ba723/master/w_600/style-guy-tom-ford-placket.jpg" alt="style-guy-tom-ford-placket.jpg"></span></div></div><div class="component-social-share default"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fare-suit-jacket-lapels-too-wide&amp;t=style-guy-tom-ford-placket.jpg"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fare-suit-jacket-lapels-too-wide&amp;t=style-guy-tom-ford-placket.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item pinterest" data-href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fare-suit-jacket-lapels-too-wide&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F56030a7a00a6dc503f9ba723%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fstyle-guy-tom-ford-placket.jpg&amp;description=style-guy-tom-ford-placket.jpg"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fare-suit-jacket-lapels-too-wide&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F56030a7a00a6dc503f9ba723%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fstyle-guy-tom-ford-placket.jpg&amp;description=style-guy-tom-ford-placket.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Pinterest"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Pinterest</span></a></div></div></div><figcaption class="caption callout-image-caption"><div class="credits">Getty Images</div></figcaption></figure></div></div><p data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.4.3"><strong>How does Tom Ford get his shirt plackets so stiff? I like the look of leaving 2 or 3 buttons un-done, but my shirt always slouches. How do I get my plackets to look crisp?</strong><br>If every American man spent at least an hour a week asking how the hell Tom Ford looks so good, we&apos;d be the world&apos;s best-dressed nation. We&apos;ve tried to steal <a href="http://www.gq.com/gallery/project-upgrade-tom-ford-makeover">Mr. Ford&apos;s style secrets</a> before, but I don&apos;t think he covered perfect shirt plackets. I can tell you how he <em>doesn&#x2019;t</em> do it&#x2014;or at least how <em>you</em> shouldn&#x2019;t: by using starch. That&#x2019;s like injecting poison into your beautiful shirt. You have two options to get that off-duty-millionaire-playboy-open-shirt look. Option A: find a shirt with a stiff, substantial collar&#x2014;the thicker, the better. That&apos;ll hold up the shirt, and let it cascade out of your lapels. Try it on in the store with your favorite blazer. Option B: If you want the Tom Ford look, splash out on a Tom Ford shirt. He is your cocktail hour spirit guide after all, right?</p><div class="embed hr" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.4.5"><hr></div><p data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.4.6"><strong>I try not to repeat outfits on Instagram. Is that silly?</strong><br>Yes.</p><div class="embed hr" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.4.7"><hr></div><div class="embed callout" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.4.8"><div class="callout omfg" data-type="callout"><figure class="embedded-image" data-type="image"><div class="image-content"><div class="component-rendition"><div class="component-image loaded"><span><img src="http://media.gq.com/photos/56030a7900a6dc503f9ba71f/master/w_806/style-guy-north-west-hip-kid.jpg" alt="style-guy-north-west-hip-kid.jpg"></span></div></div><div class="component-social-share default"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fare-suit-jacket-lapels-too-wide&amp;t=style-guy-north-west-hip-kid.jpg"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fare-suit-jacket-lapels-too-wide&amp;t=style-guy-north-west-hip-kid.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item pinterest" data-href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fare-suit-jacket-lapels-too-wide&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F56030a7900a6dc503f9ba71f%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fstyle-guy-north-west-hip-kid.jpg&amp;description=style-guy-north-west-hip-kid.jpg"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fare-suit-jacket-lapels-too-wide&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F56030a7900a6dc503f9ba71f%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fstyle-guy-north-west-hip-kid.jpg&amp;description=style-guy-north-west-hip-kid.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Pinterest"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Pinterest</span></a></div></div></div><figcaption class="caption callout-image-caption"><div class="credits">Getty Images</div></figcaption></figure>

<p><strong>My coworker has a five-year-old son that he&apos;s constantly dressing like a tiny street-style star. I think it&#x2019;s annoying and damaging to the child. What do you think?</strong><br>I get what you&#x2019;re feeling&#x2014;let a kid just be a kid. Living in N.Y.C., it&#x2019;s common to walk through SoHo and see a toddler wearing shoes that cost more mine. I get a little jealous, I&apos;ll admit. Then I check myself. I don&#x2019;t have any little StyleBabies at the moment, but if I did, I&#x2019;d teach &apos;em everything I know. And part of that would be lessons on style. If a dad can teach his little guy what sports teams to root for and what music is good, why can&apos;t he teach him how to dress? (Also: you&#x2019;re hating on a five-year-old. Maybe the problem isn&apos;t that he dresses so well, but that you got out-shined by a five-year-old?)</p></div></div></div><div class="grid" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5"><div class="row" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0"><div class="col col-sm-15" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.0"><div class="component-topics" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0"><ul data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0"><li data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0"><a href="../search?tags=Instagram" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0.0">Instagram</a></li><li data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1"><a href="../search?tags=Style%2520Guy" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1.0">Style Guy</a></li><li data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2"><a href="../search?tags=Suits" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2.0">Suits</a></li><li data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-3"><a href="../search?tags=Tom%2520Ford" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-3.0">Tom Ford</a></li></ul></div></div><div class="col col-sm-5" data-reactid=".nhk2utogsg.1.1.0.0.5.0.1"><div cla